comments.body:
I confirm that the following change does fix the crash:

```py
diff --git a/Modules/_ssl.c b/Modules/_ssl.c
index 2eb31229a9b..61282484185 100644
--- a/Modules/_ssl.c
+++ b/Modules/_ssl.c
@@ -5194,7 +5194,7 @@ _servername_callback(SSL *s, int *al, void *args)
     return ret;

 error:
-    Py_DECREF(ssl_socket);
+    Py_XDECREF(ssl_socket);
     *al = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
     ret = SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_ALERT_FATAL;
     PyGILState_Release(gstate);
```

The non-trivial part is to write a regression test :-)

@picnixz plans to write a PR to fix this issue.
